    "body": "Turns out Chrome doesn't cause the Hyper HTTP server to hang.  The shutdown simply takes a bit longer.\r\n\r\nHere's how to the `^C` looks with Firefox:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/165678/76073357-c7815b80-5f99-11ea-8b5a-d72d3bfc086c.png)\r\n\r\nAnd with Chrome:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/165678/76073400-d5cf7780-5f99-11ea-830a-b327a12c83ba.png)\r\n\r\nIt can be seen that [Chrome sends keepalives until it's connection timeout elapses](https://superuser.com/a/316453).  It's a separate confounding factor that Chrome has larger connection timeout settings than other browsers: 300 seconds compared to e.g. Firefox'es 90 (by default).\r\n\r\nMy opinion based on that is that the issue can be closed as there's nothing the built-in HTTP server does wrong.",
